The '''Batahin''' are an [[Arab]] tribe in [[Butana]], a region in [[Sudan]].<ref>{{Cite book |title=Disrupting Territories: Land, Commodification and Conflict in Sudan |first1=Richard |last1=Rottenburg |first2=Jörg |last2=Gertel |first3=Sandra |last3=Calkins |publisher=Boydell & Brewer |year=2014}}</ref> The Batahin are [[Arabic language|Arabic]]-speaking<ref>{{cite book |title=Tenants and Nomads in Eastern Sudan: A Study of Economic Adaptations in the New Halfa Scheme |first=Gunnar M. |last=Sørbø |publisher=Nordic Africa Institute |year=1985 |page=98}}</ref> [[Muslim]]s, and number about 200,000.{{when?|date=January 2015}}{{Citation needed|date=January 2015}}

