The presence of Swisses in [[Italy]] is especially on the border, [[Campione d'Italia]] and in [[Milan]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.redattoresociale.it/Notiziario/Articolo/454746/Quei-50-mila-svizzeri-in-Italia-che-nessuno-accusa-di-rubare-il-lavoro|publisher=Redattoresociale.it |language=Italian |title=Quei 50 mila svizzeri in Italia che nessuno accusa di "rubare" il lavoro |accessdate=2014-02-16 |date=16 February 2014}}</ref>

==Numbers==
In 2014 in [[Italy]] there are 8,029 regular citizens from [[Swiss]]. In 2006 there were 9,753. The three cities with most number of Swisses are: [[Milan]], [[Rome]] and [[Florence]].<ref name="int">{{cite news|url=http://www.comuni-italiani.it/statistiche/stranieri/ch.htmll|title=Comuni Italiani|date=11 January 2014|work=Comuni|accessdate=9 February 2014|language=it}}{{Dead link|date=June 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref>

